designing systems his record of success in developing successful domestic and international businesses his high level of energy optimism and belief in the mission make vince uniquely qualified to manage cii business and finance operations michael hamilton ceo michael has nearly  years of experience in information security as a practitioner consultant executive and entrepreneur as former chief information security officer for the city of seattle michael managed information security policy strategy and operations for  government agencies prior michael was the managing consultant for verisign global security consulting and in that role provided expertise for hundreds of organizations mike simon cto with an education in computer science and  years experience designing and securing information systems mike simon is a wellknown and highly respected member of the northwests information security community mike is faculty at the university of washington information school a published author a subject matter expert in the energy and finance sectors and integrated with law enforcement through contacts in the fbi dhs and infragard frederick langston cissp ccsk director of professional services fred has more than  years of professional information security experience working for hundreds of clients on projects to create effective strategies in enterprise security and data protection programs he has developed proven business and security processes that are in use hundreds of fortune  companies today advisors dennis evans kyle kincaid ken kambich unconfirmed loading informatics introduction what we do who we are our community we are informatics we are informatics we develop opensource and proprietary software for the healthcare industry and offer the expertise to put it to work new website launched informatics released its new branding via an updated website new templates and business cards what we do what we do with a focus on pragmatic solutions that can meet today’s needs while still evolving gracefully toward the needs of tomorrow informatics offers software and consulting services for early stage venture backed startups publicly traded companies and the largest nonprofit health plan in the united states software development we develop open source and proprietary software systems for the healthcare industry software as a service saas we created the terminology development environment that is used internationally by countries to develop their snomed ct extension and by the ihtsdo for snomed ct itself managed services we offer three variations of managed services to our clients software as a service saas authoring  modeling service managed subscription content software as a service saas we provide clients with the software tools and infrastructure necessary to for them to develop edit and generate periodic releases of snomed ct terminology extensions fully managed by informatics saas allows our clients to receive optimum performance without having to do the extra software maintenance legwork authoring  modeling service we provide healthcare and clinical terminology organizations with full authoring modeling editing and domainspecific refset creation support for content they seek to include in snomed ct extensions and releases managed subscription content we assist enterprises in optimizing existing infrastructure by providing fully managed subscription services to snomed ct rxnorm and loinc we help ensure that subscribers have accurate and current version updates to these foundational content terminologies for their electronic health record systems an essential part of lifecritical ehr support informatics consulting we deliver a tailored advisory experience to clients interested in obtaining high quality clinical decision support and health information management systems with consultation and design services in these areas comprehensive architecture foundational content and comprehensive tooling comprehensive architecture our consultation and design services start with discerning the project objectives and needs we then assess and document the current architecture framework and use this information to integrate into a comprehensive architecture design that homogenizes a multisystem input allowing for coordinated and compelling decision support output foundational content we provide expert assistance in selecting the necessary foundational systems such as rxnorm snomed ct or loinc upon which to build or underpin their electronic health records and clinical decision support tools comprehensive tooling we provide clients with a thorough examination of their environment and needs followed by a tailored recommendation on how to apply part or all of the cheitah suite to meet those needs we enable a transformation into an optimized and efficient clinical decision support system containing proper workflow components and comprehensive layers of foundational content education  training we train software developers knowledgebased vendors and healthcare providers on comprehensive architecture foundational content tooling software terminology authoring snomed ct we also offer education and training in the field of snomed ct terminology authoring and snomed ct extension management who we are who we are headquartered in bend oregon informatics is an independent healthcare informatics company with expertise in opensource and proprietary software development informatics architecture and design and solutions for medical and healthcare semantics keith e campbell md phd chief technology officer with more than  years of experience in health informatics and software development keith is internationally known for his work in medical terminology development and the products he has developed to solve the field’s most pressing problems keith holds a phd in medical informatics and computer science from stanford university and an md from the university of southern california prior to joining informatics keith served as the assistant national director of informatics for kaiser permanente and as the chief technology officer for inoveon susan castillo chief executive officer with more than two decades of experience in software development and executive management susan is skilled at managing software projects and designing processes that improve organizational effectiveness and increase product quality susan holds a bs in computer science and extensive onthejob training on managing people and software projects prior to forming informatics susan served as vice president of engineering for whowhere and vice president of personal and communications products for lycos her extensive background also includes seven years with apple computer as both manager of system software and member of the office of the cto our community our community we believe that the longterm health of our company is strongly connected to the health of our community therefore supporting organizations who strive to make central oregon a better place is a core tenet of our culture deschutes basin land trust the deschutes basin land trust serves the deschutes river basin an area that covers approximately  of oregon and includes several of oregon’s fastest growing counties central oregon trail alliance the central oregon trail alliance is a volunteer group that works in conjunction with the usfs blm and other land managers to build and maintain trails in bend and the surrounding area tower theater central oregons leading performing arts organization providing cultural and educational programs that make essential contributions to the regions lifestyle and strength of community britt festival britt festivals a nonprofit organization is the pacific northwests premier outdoor summer performing arts festival contact us infoinformaticscom  critical informatics  threat detection human response discover mdr managed threat detection investigation and response threat detection our software monitors your systems and network traffic × for s